  "prompt": "What are the some of the best lines in English songs?",
  "response": "There are countless memorable and impactful lines in English songs across various genres. Here are a few notable examples:\n\n1. **\"Imagine all the people living life in peace.\"** - John Lennon, \"Imagine\"\n2. **\"And in the end, the love you take is equal to the love you make.\"** - The Beatles, \"The End\"\n3. **\"You may say I'm a dreamer, but I'm not the only one.\"** - John Lennon, \"Imagine\"\n4. **\"I will always love you.\"** - Whitney Houston, \"I Will Always Love You\"\n5. **\"It's a beautiful day, don't let it get away.\"** - U2, \"Beautiful Day\"\n6. **\"We could be heroes, just for one day.\"** - David Bowie, \"Heroes\"\n7. **\"Don't stop believin', hold on to that feelin'.\"** - Journey, \"Don't Stop Believin'\"\n8. **\"Every little thing gonna be alright.\"** - Bob Marley, \"Three Little Birds\"\n9. **\"Hello from the other side.\"** - Adele, \"Hello\"\n10. **\"You can't always get what you want, but if you try sometimes, you just might find, you get what you need.\"** - The Rolling Stones, \"You Can't Always Get What You Want\"\n\nThese lines often resonate deeply with listeners and have become iconic in their own right, reflecting themes of love, peace, perseverance, and hope.",
